WebSocket endpoint for BrowserQL. Connect to establish a persistent browser
session, then send multiple GraphQL operations as JSON messages. The browser
and page state persist across all messages for the connection duration.

Messages use the same JSON format as the HTTP POST endpoint:
Send: { "query": "mutation { goto(url: \"..\") { status } }", "variables": {} }
Receive: { "data": { "goto": { "status": 200 } } }

